      "href": "/techniclrpakdrm/list/y2k-aesthetic/",
      "user": "techniclrpakdrm",
      "slug": "y2k-aesthetic",
      "title": "Y2K Aesthetic",
      "desc": "That time of American Culture where everything felt post-modern. Nobody could challenge America militarily on the world stage, the Soviet Union collapsed, China hadn’t grown into an economic powerhouse just yet, the Columbine shooting felt like an exception, 9/11 was right around the corner, & social media wasn’t ripping families apart. \n\n(Note: not all of these movies need to necessarily come out in the year 2000, they just have to be a Blue Collar Comedy or Stoner Flicks from this arbitrary time span of when the economy rebounded a bit after Stagflation/Persian Gulf War & sorta fade out after 9/11)",
      "owner": "List by TechniclrPakdrm",
      "tags": []
    },
